Package: BLENDM
Type: Package
Title: BLEND-M: Cellular Deconvolution with Personalized DNA Methylation References
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-06-03
Authors@R: person("Penghui", "Huang", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                   email = "peh57@pitt.edu")
Description: BLENDM performs reference-based cellular deconvolution of bulk DNA
    methylation (DNAm) data. Unlike existing methods that assume a shared reference
    across all samples, BLEND-M learns personalized cell-type-specific (CTS) reference
    profiles for each bulk sample by blending available purified reference data. It
    explicitly models heteroscedasticity across marker CpGs via a two-step
    inverse-variance weighted non-negative least squares estimator, improving
    robustness to noisy markers. The package also provides a two-step marker CpG
    selection procedure that identifies CpGs with strong cell-type specificity.
